  119-
  120:### OpenJDK (i.e. non-Android)
  121-
  122-#### Native Classifiers
  123-
  124:The OpenJDK artifacts are platform-dependent since each embeds a native library for a particular
  125-platform. We publish artifacts to Maven Central for the following platforms:
  126-
  127-Classifier | OS | Architecture
  128------------| ------- | ---------------- |
  129-linux-x86_64 | Linux | x86_64 (64-bit)
  130-osx-x86_64 | Mac | x86_64 (64-bit)
  131-windows-x86 | Windows | x86 (32-bit)
  132-windows-x86_64 | Windows | x86_64 (64-bit)
  133-
  134-#### Maven
  135-
  136-Use the [os-maven-plugin](https://github.com/trustin/os-maven-plugin) to add the dependency:
  137-
  138-```xml
  139-<build>
  140-  <extensions>
  141-    <extension>
  142-      <groupId>kr.motd.maven</groupId>
  143-      <artifactId>os-maven-plugin</artifactId>
  144-      <version>1.4.1.Final</version>
  145-    </extension>
  146-  </extensions>
  147-</build>
  148-
  149-<dependency>
  150-  <groupId>org.conscrypt</groupId>
  151-  <artifactId>conscrypt-openjdk</artifactId>
  152-  <version>2.5.2</version>
  153-  <classifier>${os.detected.classifier}</classifier>
  154-</dependency>
  155-```
  156-
  157-#### Gradle
  158-Use the [osdetector-gradle-plugin](https://github.com/google/osdetector-gradle-plugin)
  159-(which is a wrapper around the os-maven-plugin) to add the dependency:
  160-
  161-```gradle
  162-buildscript {
  163-  repositories {
  164-    mavenCentral()
  165-  }
  166-  dependencies {
  167-    classpath 'com.google.gradle:osdetector-gradle-plugin:1.4.0'
  168-  }
  169-}
  170-
  171-// Use the osdetector-gradle-plugin
  172-apply plugin: "com.google.osdetector"
  173-
  174-dependencies {
  175-  compile 'org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk:2.5.2:' + osdetector.classifier
  176-}
  177-```
  178-
  179-#### Uber JAR
  180-
  181-For convenience, we also publish an Uber JAR to Maven Central that contains the shared
  182-libraries for all of the published platforms. While the overall size of the JAR is
  183-larger than depending on a platform-specific artifact, it greatly simplifies the task of
  184-dependency management for most platforms.
  185-
  186-To depend on the uber jar, simply use the `conscrypt-openjdk-uber` artifacts.
  187-
